1. HTML Basics

Q1: What is HTML?

HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard language used to create web pages.
It structures content using elements like headings, paragraphs, images, and links.

 Purpose:

Structure web content
Display text, images, videos
Create web page layout

Q2: Basic Structure of HTML Document
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Page</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello World</h1>
</body>
</html>

Mandatory Tags:

<html> → Root element
<head> → Metadata (title, links)
<title> → Page title
<body> → Visible content

Q3: Block vs Inline Elements

Block Elements	Inline Elements
Take full width	        Take only needed width
Start on new line	Stay in same line

 Examples:

Block: <div>, <p>, <h1>
Inline: <span>, <a>, <img>
Q4: Semantic HTML

 Semantic HTML gives meaning to content.

Importance:

Better SEO
Better accessibility
Easy for developers

 Examples:

<header>
<footer>
<main>
<article>
<section>


 Lab Code
