 4. CSS Selectors

Q1: CSS Selector

Used to select HTML elements.

p { color: red; }       /* element */
.class { color: blue; } /* class */
#id { color: green; }   /* id */

Q2: Specificity

Priority:
 Inline > ID > Class > Element

Q3: CSS Types

Type	Advantage	Disadvantage
Inline	Quick	Not reusable
Internal	Simple	Not scalable
External	Best practice	Needs file

 External CSS Example
form {
    background: lightgray;
    padding: 20px;
}

input, textarea {
    margin: 10px;
}

button:hover {
    background: green;
    color: white;
}

 5. CSS Box Model


Components:

